                <div class="inquiry-section">
                    <h2>Course Inquiry: Why Are We So Attracted to Stories?</h2>
                    <p>What is the power of storytelling? This is the central question driving our exploration in English 1007. As humans, we're naturally drawn to stories—we seek them out, create them, and find them everywhere we go. From ancient myths to modern internet legends, we transform our experiences and the world around us into narratives that help us make sense of reality.</p>
                    
                    <p>Stories have an incredible ability to connect us, to make us feel understood, and to shape our beliefs and behaviors. They work across all contexts—in marketing, education, entertainment, sports narratives, and even our personal relationships. Once you figure out your story, you can reach people in profound ways because storytelling is fundamental to human nature.</p>
                    
                    <p>However, there's a darker side to this power. Some stories can run amok, spreading beyond their intended boundaries and causing real harm. The Slenderman case serves as a perfect and tragic example: an internet creepypasta evolved from harmless fiction into something that influenced vulnerable minds with devastating consequences. This course examines both the magic and the danger of storytelling in our digital age, asking us to consider: How do we harness the power of stories responsibly? How do we protect against narratives that blur the line between fiction and reality?</p>
                </div>
                
